data.enText: an amount of bread that has been shaped and baked in one piece

data.id-g-sent: half a loaf is better than no bread

data.chText: 游手好闲；无所事事；闲荡
data.enText: to spend your time not doing anything, especially when you should be working

data.chText: 一群小孩在外面四处游荡。
data.enText: A group of kids were loafing around outside.
half a loaf is better than no bread

data.chText: 半块面包比没有面包强；聊胜于无
data.enText: you should be grateful for sth, even if it is not as good, much, etc. as you really wanted; something is better than nothing

data.chText: 你动动脑子；你仔细想想
data.enText: used to tell sb to think about sth, especially when they have asked for your opinion or said sth stupid

data.chText: “你为什么不愿再见到他？”“唔，你好好想想吧！”
data.enText: ‘Why don't you want to see him again?’ ‘Oh, use your head!’

data.chText: 源自同韵俚语loaf of bread，代表head的意思 。
data.enText: From rhyming slang, in which loaf of bread stands for ‘head’.

tr: a quantity of food (other than bread) formed in a particular shape
a shaped mass of baked bread that is usually sliced before eating

example: The high school students like to loiter in the Central Square
Who is this man that is hanging around the department?
Her son is just bumming around all day

value.boxr_value: The plural form of the noun is loaves. Loafs is the third person singular present tense of the verb. 名词复数为loaves。loafs为动词的第三人称单数现在式。

value.def: A loaf of bread is bread which has been shaped and baked in one piece. It is usually large enough for more than one person and can be cut into slices.
If you loaf, you stand or wait in a place, not doing anything interesting or useful.

example.ex: We had been at Cambridge together, she studying medicine and me loafing around.
example.tran: 我们一起在剑桥呆过。她学医，我则无所事事。
